=== ExpCraftWeb ===

If ExpCraft is configured to store player experience in MySQL database this
project can be used to display their progress.

==== Installation ====

- Check out ExpCraftWeb
- Compile it with maven
- The created JAR contains all the files necessary to run the page
  <project>/target/*.jar
- copy the JAR to you web server alias and extract it
- rename the config.php.default to config.php and set the database connection

==== Migration from LevelCraft ====

If you have been using LevelCraft, you can run the migrate-from-levelcraft.sql
database script to create a ExpCraft table with the values from LevelCraft.

Execute
mysql -u [minecraft user] -p [password] [minecraft database] < migrate-from-levelcraft.sql
